The paper deals with approximation algorithms for revenue maximization in the context of item pricing, which is a central topic in computational game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic economics (cs.EC). The techniques used in the paper involve data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), as well as machine learning and optimization (cs.AI, cs.LG).
